Coalition Of South East Youth Leaders (COSEYL) has condemned the moves by Nigeria Police Headquarters, Abuja, to relocate the Police Area Command, Ebem Ohafia to Arochukwu local government area. The president-general of the coalition, Mr Goodluck Ibem, stated this in an exclusive interview with LEADERSHIP in Umuahia, the Abia state capital, saying the move is unjustified. He said the police announced the move to remove the command from the headquarters of Ohafia local government council following a recent attack on the police station and the High Court. The attack was in response to the killing of one Friday Arunsi by Police Constable Christopher Ugwu, adding that the dastardly act was the handiwork of enemies of the community. “Based on investigations conducted so far and confirmed by the new commissioner of Police (CP), Mrs Janet Agbede, the destruction was not perpetrated by the indigenes of the community. He explained that relocating the command will put the people of Ohafia into serious hardship as there is no good motorable road to Arochukwu except through Akwa Ibom state in the South East zone. “We therefore call on the Inspector General of Police (IGP), Mr Muhammadu Adamu  to reconsider the decision, maintaining that it will amount to punishing the people for a sin they did not commit.